                    },
                    "body": "Assigning to myself, since this is something I've wanted to see implemented for a while now.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-01T04:06:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-01T04:06:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16515",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Attaching patch for this as ZF-1755.patch.\n\nOriginally I wanted to just change the index for the $_custom array to use the columnName value, but I realized that this would break backwards-compatibility if somebody tries to retrieve a column by it's numeric index (which is probably not the best idea...).\n\nInstead, I implemented a new array called $_customByName that uses the new indexing method. There's several additional functions added on to support this behavior and make sure that malformed data doesn't get inserted accidently. The old $_custom array is still maintained, just in case anybody wants to use it.\n\nRyan, would you please review these changes?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-01T08:29:31.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-01T08:29:31.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16521",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've uploaded a new patch ([^ZF-1755_v2.patch]) to correct Ryan's concerns (sent via email), as well as a few things I noticed myself:\n\n- Added functions to remove custom elements.\n- Noticed that a few unit tests weren't being run.\n- Fixed a bug that could cause the $_custom and $_customByName arrays to get out of sync.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=tjohns",
                        "name": "tjohns",
                        "displayName": "Trevor Johns",
                        "active": true
